### Test Google Meet Configuration Fix
### This test helps verify that the Google Meet configuration is correct

@baseUrl = https://localhost:7001
@studentToken = YOUR_STUDENT_TOKEN_HERE

### 1. Test Google Meet Link Generation
### Expected Results:
### - If using API key (AIzaSy...): Error message in logs + fallback link
### - If using service account private key: Real working Google Meet link
### - If not configured: Warning message in logs + fallback link

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/meeting/google-meet
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "React Development Session - Configuration Test",
  "description": "Testing Google Meet configuration with proper service account setup",
  "duration": 60,
  "platform": "google-meet",
  "startTime": "2024-12-25T10:00:00Z"
}

### 2. Check the Response
### Look for:
### - If URL starts with https://meet.google.com/ and has a valid format
### - If the URL actually works when opened in a browser
### - Check the API logs for success/error messages

### 3. Validate the Generated Link
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/meeting/validate
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "url": "{{response.body.url}}"
}

### Expected Validation Results:
### - Real Google Meet links: isValid = true
### - Fallback/fake links: isValid = false or true (depending on format)
